01:49.629 --> 01:52.831
You were up early this morning.

01:52.866 --> 01:54.733
Garbage trucks woke me.

01:54.767 --> 01:56.168
Figured I might as well
get a jump on things.

01:56.202 --> 01:57.169
New case?

01:57.203 --> 01:58.804
Not yet.

02:01.674 --> 02:03.142
- Hayes.
- Hmm?

02:03.176 --> 02:04.443
Everything okay?

02:06.679 --> 02:08.113
Yes.

02:10.683 --> 02:12.117
Mm.

02:16.523 --> 02:17.990
You remember when we first met?

02:18.024 --> 02:20.125
Of course.

02:20.160 --> 02:21.627
Why?

02:21.661 --> 02:22.995
Just wondering why you liked me.

02:23.029 --> 02:24.830
Too many reasons to count.

02:24.864 --> 02:26.131
I'd settle for top three.

02:27.133 --> 02:30.235
Smarts, attitude, beauty.

02:32.038 --> 02:33.105
I can continue.

02:33.139 --> 02:34.907
You'll tell me later.

02:36.009 --> 02:38.844
Ever since your dad left,
you've seemed a little...

02:38.878 --> 02:41.046
No. I'm good.

02:41.080 --> 02:42.648
Great, actually.

02:55.228 --> 02:56.728
Gerald Harris.

02:56.763 --> 02:58.730
Serving life for murdering
his wife, Claire.

02:58.765 --> 03:01.200
Where'd this case come from?
I don't remember logging it.

03:01.234 --> 03:02.167
Claire died after a fall

03:02.202 --> 03:04.036
from a second-story balcony
in their home.

03:04.070 --> 03:05.671
Prosecution claimed that she fell

03:05.705 --> 03:07.673
after a blow from the head
delivered by Gerald.

03:07.707 --> 03:09.074
Was there a problem with the forensics?

03:09.108 --> 03:10.576
Not that I'm aware of.

03:10.610 --> 03:14.079
No witnesses to the crime, so no
chance for witness misidentification.

03:14.113 --> 03:15.681
Right you are.

03:15.715 --> 03:17.015
So what's the issue with the conviction?

03:18.751 --> 03:21.520
Gerald's defense attorney
really screwed the pooch.

03:21.544 --> 03:23.598
_

03:25.391 --> 03:26.992
Criminal courthouse, fast as you can.

03:28.628 --> 03:30.374
Oh, uh, one stop on the way...

03:30.399 --> 03:32.164
Smithson's Dry Cleaner on Cicero.

03:38.238 --> 03:39.669
Kind of in a hurry.

03:39.694 --> 03:41.573
I wanted to say I had fun last night.

03:41.608 --> 03:43.075
That's sweet. Me, too.

03:43.109 --> 03:44.710
Maybe I could get your number.

03:44.744 --> 03:45.844
I'd like to see you again.

03:45.878 --> 03:48.747
It was fun, but not repeatbusiness fun.

03:48.781 --> 03:50.015
Move! Go!

03:50.984 --> 03:52.284
"Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,

03:52.318 --> 03:55.887
my client, Gerald Harris,
devoted husband,

03:55.922 --> 03:58.056
woke up one morning last November

03:58.091 --> 04:00.025
to a terrible tragedy.

04:00.059 --> 04:05.764
His beloved wife, Claire, was dead."

04:05.798 --> 04:08.600
"Ladies and gentlemen of the jury..."

04:11.938 --> 04:14.773
Testing my patience
on the first day, Ms. Morrison?

04:14.807 --> 04:15.974
Hardly seems prudent.

04:16.009 --> 04:17.776
Million apologies, Your Honor.

04:17.810 --> 04:18.877
Good morning, Gerald.

04:18.911 --> 04:21.178
Well...

04:25.351 --> 04:27.185
You're not ASA Rachel Johnson.

04:30.990 --> 04:33.392
Nothing gets by you.

04:33.426 --> 04:34.793
Conner Wallace.

04:34.827 --> 04:36.128
Rachel went into labor a month early.

04:36.162 --> 04:37.896
And I just thought she was fat.

04:39.299 --> 04:41.133
I'm a big fan of your father's.
He's a hero of mine.

04:41.167 --> 04:42.901
Well, that makes one of us.

04:42.935 --> 04:45.304
I hear you're the golden boy...
Mr. Undefeated.

04:45.338 --> 04:47.839
Don't get used to it.

04:47.874 --> 04:49.606
I'm gonna kick your ass.

